## Implementation Details

### Why This Approach?
1. **React Instead of Next.js**: The project uses Vite as the build tool with React, not Next.js. The `/react` export path is the correct choice for this framework setup.
2. **AppContent Root Placement**: The Analytics and SpeedInsights components are rendered at the root level of the app content, ensuring they monitor all page views and performance metrics across the entire application.
3. **No Manual Route Support Needed**: The `@vercel/analytics/react` package automatically handles route detection through React Router when the components are rendered at the application root.

### What These Components Do
- **Analytics**: Collects Web Vitals data (LCP, FID, CLS, etc.) and sends anonymous analytics to Vercel's dashboard
- **SpeedInsights**: Provides real-time performance monitoring and insights at the application level

### How to Enable Data Collection
After deploying to Vercel:
1. Go to your [Vercel dashboard](https://vercel.com/dashboard)
2. Select your Spotify project
3. Click the **Analytics** tab
4. Click **Enable** if not already enabled
5. The app will start collecting analytics data after the next deployment

### Key Configuration Notes
- No additional configuration files needed - the components work with sensible defaults
- Route support is automatic through React Router integration
- Web Vitals collection is automatic - no manual event tracking required for basic metrics
- Custom events can be added later using the `@vercel/analytics` package's event tracking API if needed

